- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis for hate speech detection. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper involves analyzing images in addition to text. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the dataset is collected from Twitter, a social network platform. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with multimodal publications consisting of both text and images. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper proposes different models for hate speech detection and compares their performance.
